race.comment: SECOND NATURE (2) ran a nice race last time out, finishing second and beaten only a head over 1968m at Yarra Valley as favourite after being prominent at the turn. Has strong prospects in this lineup. ADARE MANOR (3) is third up and will be better for the solid effort at Wangaratta over this trip. Has a low gate, and the go-to hoop replaces the apprentice. Ready to win. PARABELLUM (5) found a heavy track and belted the 52 graders at Wangaratta by 4.5L over this distance. May get conditions to suit and is a decent chance if she does. GRUNNETTAN (1) recorded his Maiden win three back and is ready to score again after a couple of minor placings. The latest was at Kilmore, and he won't find this as tough. PENDANTE (4) has a 2kg claim and is going well enough to consider.
